  "local_port": 57890,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Are there any websites like DAAD for masters in US?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several websites and resources similar to DAAD (Deutscher Akademischer Austauschdienst) that provide information and support for pursuing a master's degree in the United States. Here are a few notable ones:\n\n1. **EducationUSA**:\n   - **Website**: [www.educationusa.state.gov](https://www.educationusa.state.gov)\n   - **Description**: A U.S. Department of State network of over 430 international student advising centers in more than 175 countries. EducationUSA provides comprehensive information about U.S. higher education institutions, admission processes, scholarships, and visa requirements.\n\n2. **Institute of International Education (IIE)**:\n   - **Website**: [www.iie.org](https://www.iie.org)\n   - **Description**: IIE is a non-profit organization that administers a wide range of scholarship and exchange programs. Their website offers resources for students seeking to study in the U.S., including program finders and scholarship databases.\n\n3. **Fulbright Program**:\n   - **Website**: [www.foreign.fulbrightonline.org](https://foreign.fulbrightonline.org)\n   - **Description**: The Fulbright Program offers grants for international students to pursue graduate studies in the U.S. The website provides detailed information on application processes, eligibility criteria, and available fields of study.\n\n4. **CollegeBoard**:\n   - **Website**: [www.collegeboard.org](https://www.collegeboard.org)\n   - **Description**: Known for standardized tests like the SAT and AP, CollegeBoard also provides resources for graduate school admissions, including program search tools and financial aid information.\n\n5. **GradSchools.com**:\n   - **Website**: [www.gradschools.com](https://www.gradschools.com)\n   - **Description**: A comprehensive directory of graduate programs in the U.S., including master's degrees. The site allows users to search by field of study, location, and other criteria.\n\n6. **Peterson's**:\n   - **Website**: [www.petersons.com](https://www.petersons.com)\n   - **Description**: Peterson's offers a wealth of resources for graduate school applicants, including program search tools, test preparation materials, and advice on the application process.\n\n7. **ProFellow**:\n   - **Website**: [www.profellow.com](https://www.profellowship.com)\n   - **Description**: ProFellow provides information on fellowships and scholarships for graduate studies in the U.S. The site is particularly useful for finding funding opportunities.\n\nThese platforms can help you navigate the process of applying to master's programs in the United States, from finding the right program to securing funding and understanding visa requirements.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
